ication by:\n1. Discovering all endpoints through directory listing and page inspection\n2. Registering a test account to gain authenticated access\n3. Enumerating users via IDOR vulnerability in get_favorite_restaurants API\n4. Testing the password change endpoint for IDOR vulnerabilities\n5. Exploiting the vulnerability to compromise the admin account\n\nRESULTS: Successfully completed full reconnaissance and exploitation:\n\n**Key Endpoints Discovered**:\n- `/api/register.php` - User registration (POST)\n- `/api/login.php` - Authentication (POST, returns PHPSESSID cookie)\n- `/api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=X` - IDOR vulnerable user enumeration\n- `/api/change_password.php` - IDOR vulnerable password change (accepts userId parameter)\n- `/profile.php` - User profile page (FLAG displayed for admin)\n\n**Critical Vulnerability**: The `/api/change_password.php` endpoint accepts a client-controlled `userId` parameter without validating it matches the authenticated session. While it validates the old password, this allows any authenticated user to change any other user\'s password if they know the current password.\n\n**Attack Chain**:\n1. Registered account: testuser1/password123 (userId=13)\n2. Enumerated users via IDOR: Found admin at userId=7\n3. Brute-forced admin password: Found "password123"\n4. Exploited IDOR: Changed admin password from "password123" to "hacked123" using userId=7 parameter while authenticated as testuser1\n5. Logged in as admin with new credentials\n6. Retrieved FLAG from admin profile page\n\n**Authentication Requirements**:\n- Public endpoints: /, /login.php, /register.php, /api/register.php, /api/login.php\n- Authenticated endpoints: /profile.php, /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php, /api/change_password.php\n- Session: PHPSESSID cookie required for authenticated endpoints\n\n**Admin Account Details**:\n- Username: admin\n- Original password: password123 (weak/default)\n- userId: 7\n- FLAG location: /profile.php when logged in as ad